properties.sfomuseum:description: Flight information packet issued by BOAC (British Overseas Airways Corporation) in association with Qantas Empire Airways, South African Airways, and Tasman Empire Airways Limited, titled “Your Speedbird companion”, comprising:a. folder with pockets;b. postcard with black and white photographic image of Boeing 377 Stratocruiser in flight;c. postcard with black and white photographic image of Lockheed L-649 Constellation in flight;d. postcard with black and white illustration of cutaway view of Short Solent (Hythe Speedbird);e. postcard with black and white illustration of cutaway view of Avro aircraft (York Sleeper);f. postcard with black and white illustration of cutaway view of Short Solent (Plymouth Speedbird);g. postcard with black and white illustration of cutaway view of Handley Page Halifax (Halton Speedbird);h. postcard with black and white illustration of cutaway view of Lockheed Constellation (Constellation Speedbird);i. notepad with four sheets of paper;j. route map showing international service routes for British Airways divisions; bi-fold format;k. stationery;l. brochure with information about Speedbird service; fold-out format;m. brochure titled “The story of the empty seat”; bi-fold format;n. brochure titled “Flowers are more brilliant in Bermuda”; bi-fold format;o. brochure titled “Playing is more fun in Bermuda”; bi-fold format;p. airline safety pamphlet titled “We can’t be too careful”; fold-out format;q. brochure titled “Bermuda invites you”; fold-out format;r. brochure titled “Key to Bermuda”; fold-out format.
